Package itemsInArrea

Class Route

java.lang.Object
itemsInArrea.Route
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Route>, Validate
public class Route extends Object implements Validate, Comparable<Route>
The Route class represents a route with various attributes such as id, name, coordinates, creation date, starting and ending locations, and distance.

This class implements the Validate interface to ensure that a Route instance is valid, and the Comparable interface to compare two Route objects based on their id.

  • Method Details

    • validate

      public boolean validate()
      Validates the properties of the Route object.

      A valid Route must have: - an id greater than 0, - a non-null, non-empty name, - a non-null creation date, - non-null and valid coordinates, - a non-null starting location, - a distance greater than 1.

      Specified by:
      validate in interface Validate
      Returns:
      true if the Route is valid; false otherwise.
